items.title: Punjab & Sind Bank Q3 profit surges 19% YoY
items.description: State-run Punjab & Sind Bank on Saturday reported a 19% increase in net profit to ₹336 crore in the December quarter as bad loans declined. The Delhi-headquartered bank had earned a net profit of ₹282 crore a year ago.

items.title: UCO Bank Q3 profit rises 16% YoY to Rs 739 crore
items.description: UCO Bank's net profit surged 16% to Rs 739 crore in the third quarter, driven by a 11% rise in net interest income. The bank also saw its non-performing assets ratio decline to 2.4% and gross advances grow 17%, supported by strong retail, agriculture, and MSME loan expansion.
